you have a friend.
whether its your gender or not.
whom you dont think that you can live without.
even though youve only known them for a short period of time.
doesnt it seem wrong?
doesnt it seem like it isnt suposed to happen.
and on top of that all youve never even met them in person.
it feels wrong.
it makes me think that im one of those obessive people.
who finds someone who they think is cute. 
starts talking to them.
becomes totally into them.
and then in the end.
they still dont get them.
ive been trying for a few years now to find "the one"
but from what ive been through..
and from what ive learned..
i honestly dont know if there even is someone called "the one"//"your soulmate"
i just cant believe it.
yeah im in highschool.
and yeah  my parents tell me im to young.
but times have changed.
them at 16 and me at 16 are to comepletely different things.
i dont think that they were doing even half the things i do now.
did they have jobs that most seniors and over dont have? no.
did they have as much experience in the sexual area as i do? probably not.
did they even know what the term cunt meant at this age? nope.
because back then things were sooo much easier than then are now.
back in the day they could be 18 or in their early 20s by the time they were doing what i am now.
i just cant believe how things change.
but all in all im really falling for this guy.
is that bad?
